<length_400>
Matt Palmer leads Developer Relations at Replit, empowering ambitious individuals through "vibe coding"—his evidence-based approach to AI-assisted development. A former Senior Data Engineer with Physics & Economics background from Swarthmore, he created 'Vibe Coding 101' reaching 60,000+ students globally. Palmer democratizes coding through practical tutorials and Replit's AI tools, making software creation accessible to all skill levels.
</length_400>

<length_1000>
Matt Palmer is Lead of Developer Relations at Replit, where he empowers ambitious individuals with actionable, evidence-based strategies for growth through accessible "vibe coding." Since February 2024, he's spearheaded technical content and product marketing while developing key industry partnerships. Palmer's career journey from Senior Data Engineer to developer advocate showcases his commitment to democratizing software creation. With a Physics and Economics degree from Swarthmore College, he bridges technical depth with educational accessibility. Through his YouTube channel (@mattpalmer) and as producer/instructor for 'Vibe Coding 101' with DeepLearningAI (reaching 60,000+ students globally), he champions AI-assisted development where developers leverage AI for significant coding tasks while focusing on application architecture. Palmer's philosophy emphasizes empathy for the developer journey, authenticity in content, and community building—viewing AI as a powerful productivity enhancer that lowers barriers to software creation for all skill levels.
</length_1000>
</character_descriptions>

